n is partially present.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Typed Client `runtime/v1alpha1`\n\n**Spec file:** `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go`\n**Actual file:** `client-go/clientset/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go` (also `client.go`, `interfaces.go`)\n\n| Requirement | Status | Details |\n|---|---|---|\n| File path with `versioned/` | **DIFFERENT** | Path is `clientset/typed/...` not `clientset/versioned/typed/...` |\n| `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` with `RESTClient() rest.Interface` | **MISSING** | No `RESTClient()` method anywhere; `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` in `interfaces.go` line 34-37 only has `AgentRuntimes()` and `CodeInterpreters()` |\n| `AgentRuntimesGetter` interface | **MISSING** | No such interface defined |\n| `CodeInterpretersGetter` interface | **MISSING** | No such interface defined |\n| REST defaults (GroupVersion, APIPath, negotiated serializer) | **MISSING** | No `rest.Config`, no `rest.Interface`, no serializer -- this is a fake in-memory store, not a REST client |\n| `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` struct | **DIFFERENT** | Exists (line 20-24 of `client.go`) but holds `*ObjectStore` instead of `rest.Interface` |\n\n**Verdict: SIGNIFICANTLY DIFFERENT** -- The entire approach is an in-memory fake store, not a REST-based typed client.\n\n---\n\n## 3. AgentRuntimeInterface\n\n**Spec file:** `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`\n**Actual file:** `client-go/clientset/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/interfaces.go` (interface) + `runtime_client.go` (implementation)\n\n| Requirement | Status | Details |\n|---|---|---|\n| `AgentRuntimesGetter` interface | **MISSING** | Not defined anywhere |\n| `Create` method | **MET** | `interfaces.go` line 13; implemented `runtime_client.go` line 127 |\n| `Update` method | **MET** | `interfaces.go` line 14; implemented `runtime_client.go` line 135 |\n| `UpdateStatus` method | **MET** | `interfaces.go` line 15; implemented `runtime_client.go` line 143 (delegates to Update) |\n| `Delete` method | **