{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775832163491,"sessionID":"ses_2882b03e5ffe0qgNxH0zdvDDhW","part":{"id":"prt_d77d862e8001XKbsZyS63AHHpJ","messageID":"msg_d77d84cae001pTIIWqShkLjL23","sessionID":"ses_2882b03e5ffe0qgNxH0zdvDDhW","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_3c284dbad66c48849b8b43aa","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/session-routing/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/session-routing/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Session Routing Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Route HTTP invocation traffic to sandboxes by session: resolve or create sessions via the workload manager, track activity in the store, reverse-proxy to pod endpoints, and sign outbound requests with JWT when targeting sandboxes.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Session resolution and creation\n9: The system SHALL read session id from request header `x-agentcube-session-id`. When the header is empty, the system SHALL POST to the workload manager to create a sandbox. When non-empty, the system SHALL load `SandboxInfo` from the store by session id.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Missing session triggers workload manager create\n12: - **GIVEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set and an invocation request has no `x-agentcube-session-id`\n13: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySession` runs for `AgentRuntimeKind`\n14: - **THEN** the client POSTs JSON `{\"kind\":\"AgentRuntime\",\"name\":...,\"namespace\":...}` to `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/agent-runtime`\n15: \n16: #### Scenario: Unknown session returns not found\n17: - **GIVEN** a non-empty session id not present in store\n18: - **WHEN** the store returns `ErrNotFound`\n19: - **THEN** the error maps to `NewSessionNotFoundError(sessionID)` and the HTTP handler responds using API status (typically 404)\n20: \n21: ### Requirement: Workload manager URL and auth token for creates\n22: The system SHALL require environment variable `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` at session manager construction (non-empty). When the file `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` exists and is readable, the system SHALL attach `Authorization: Bearer <trimmed contents>` to create requests.\n23: \n24: #### Scenario: Missing WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL fails startup\n25: - **GIVEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is unset\n26: - **WHEN** `NewSessionManager` is called\n27: - **THEN** it returns error `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL environment variable is not set`\n28: \n29: ### Requirement: Create response validation\n30: The system SHALL accept workload manager HTTP 200 with body `CreateSandboxResponse`; SHALL reject with internal error if `sessionId` in body is empty; SHALL build in-memory `SandboxInfo` with `SandboxID`, `Name` (= `sandboxName`), `SessionID`, `EntryPoints` from the response (other fields may be zero).\n31: \n32: #### Scenario: Non-OK from workload manager\n33: - **GIVEN** workload manager returns HTTP 404\n34: - **WHEN** the session manager handles the response\n35: - **THEN** the error is `NewSandboxTemplateNotFoundError(namespace, name, kind)`\n36: \n37: ### Requirement: Reverse proxy to sandbox\n38: The system SHALL determine upstream URL from `SandboxInfo.EntryPoints` by first matching `path` prefix against the invocation path; if none match, SHALL use the first entry point. The system SHALL build URL by prefixing `protocol` (lowercase) and `://` to `endpoint` when protocol is set and endpoint lacks a scheme. The system SHALL use `httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy`, shared `http.Transport` on the proxy, and custom `Director` to set path, host, forwarding headers, and optional JWT.\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: No entry points\n41: - **GIVEN** `EntryPoints` is empty\n42: - **WHEN** upstream is determined\n43: - **THEN** the handler responds 404 JSON `{\"error\":\"no entry point found for sandbox\"}`\n44: \n45: ### Requirement: JWT injection for sandbox kinds\n46: For sandbox kinds `Sandbox` and `SandboxClaim`, the system SHALL generate a JWT before proxying and SHALL set `Authorization: Bearer <token>` on the proxied request.\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: Signing failure\n49: - **GIVEN** JWT generation returns an error\n50: - **WHEN** forwarding is attempted\n51: - **THEN** the handler responds 500 with JSON containing `\"code\":\"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\"` and `\"error\":\"failed to sign request\"`\n52: \n53: ### Requirement: Forwarding headers and response header\n54: The system SHALL set `X-Forwarded-Host` from the incoming request host, `X-Forwarded-Proto` to `https` when TLS is present else `http`, and `X-Forwarded-For` by appending client IP to any existing values. The system SHALL set response header `x-agentcube-session-id` to the resolved session id on all proxied responses.\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Path normalization\n57: - **GIVEN** the Gin path param is non-empty and lacks a leading slash\n58: - **WHEN** the director runs\n59: - **THEN** the outbound path is prefixed with `/`\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: Proxy error mapping\n62: The system SHALL map proxy errors containing `connection refused` to 502 `{\"error\":\"sandbox unreachable\"}`, containing `timeout` to 504 `{\"error\":\"sandbox timeout\"}`, and other errors to 502 `{\"error\":\"sandbox unreachable\"}`.\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Downstream connection refused\n65: - **GIVEN** the reverse proxy fails with an error whose message includes `connection refused`\n66: - **WHEN** `ErrorHandler` runs\n67: - **THEN** status is 502 and error text is `sandbox unreachable`\n68: \n69: ### Requirement: Last-activity updates\n70: The system SHALL call `UpdateSessionLastActivity` with `time.Now()` after successfully resolving the sandbox and again after `forwardToSandbox` returns (twice per successful invoke path). Failures SHALL be logged as warnings only.\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: Store update failure does not block proxy\n73: - **GIVEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` returns an error\n74: - **WHEN** handling continues\n75: - **THEN** the proxy still runs if sandbox resolution succeeded\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: Health endpoints\n78: The system SHALL expose `GET /health/live` returning 200 `{\"status\":\"alive\"}`. The system SHALL expose `GET /health/ready` returning 200 `{\"status\":\"ready\"}` when session manager is non-nil, else 503 with `status` and `error` fields.\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Ready depends on session manager\n81: - **GIVEN** `sessionManager` is nil\n82: - **WHEN** `GET /health/ready` is served\n83: - **THEN** status is 503 and body includes `\"error\":\"session manager not available\"`\n84: \n85: ### Requirement: Concurrency limiting\n86: The system SHALL apply a semaphore middleware to `/v1/*` routes with capacity `MaxConcurrentRequests` (default 1000 when config value ≤ 0). When no slot is available, the system SHALL respond 429 JSON `{\"error\":\"server overloaded, please try again later\",\"code\":\"SERVER_OVERLOADED\"}` and abort.\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Default limit when zero in config\n89: - **GIVEN** `NewServer` receives `MaxConcurrentRequests` 0\n90: - **WHEN** the server is constructed\n91: - **THEN** the effective limit is set to 1000 before route registration\n92: \n93: ### Requirement: Invocation route surface\n94: The system SHALL register GET and POST for `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` and for `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path`, with Gin logger, recovery, and concurrency middleware on the `/v1` group only.\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: Kind passed to session lookup\n97: - **GIVEN** agent-runtime invocation\n98: - **WHEN** `handleInvoke` runs\n99: - **THEN** kind argument is `AgentRuntime` (`types.AgentRuntimeKind`)\n100: \n101: ### Requirement: HTTP server behavior\n102: The system SHALL serve with `h2c` and `http2.Server`, `ReadTimeout` 30s, `IdleTimeout` 90s; on context cancel SHALL shutdown within 10s. Optional TLS SHALL require both cert and key paths.\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: TLS misconfiguration\n105: - **GIVEN** `EnableTLS` true and empty cert path\n106: - **WHEN** `Start` runs\n107: - **THEN** it returns error stating cert/key not provided\n108: \n109: ### Requirement: Identity secret bootstrap for JWT\n110: On server creation the system SHALL construct `JWTManager`, call `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret`, and fail server creation if that returns error (except in-cluster skip path returns nil when not in cluster).\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: In-cluster secret creation\n113: - **GIVEN** in-cluster config succeeds and secret does not exist\n114: - **WHEN** `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret` runs\n115: - **THEN** it creates opaque secret `picod-router-identity` in namespace from `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` or `default` with keys `private.pem` and `public.pem`\n\n(End of file - total 115 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Session Routing Specification\n\n## Purpose\nRoute HTTP invocation traffic to sandboxes by session: resolve or create sessions via the workload manager, track activity in the store, reverse-proxy to pod endpoints, and sign outbound requests with JWT when targeting sandboxes.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Session resolution and creation\nThe system SHALL read session id from request header `x-agentcube-session-id`. When the header is empty, the system SHALL POST to the workload manager to create a sandbox. When non-empty, the system SHALL load `SandboxInfo` from the store by session id.\n\n#### Scenario: Missing session triggers workload manager create\n- **GIVEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set and an invocation request has no `x-agentcube-session-id`\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySession` runs for `AgentRuntimeKind`\n- **THEN** the client POSTs JSON `{\"kind\":\"AgentRuntime\",\"name\":...,\"namespace\":...}` to `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/agent-runtime`\n\n#### Scenario: Unknown session returns not found\n- **GIVEN** a non-empty session id not present in store\n- **WHEN** the store returns `ErrNotFound`\n- **THEN** the error maps to `NewSessionNotFoundError(sessionID)` and the HTTP handler responds using API status (typically 404)\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"specs/session-routing/spec.md","time":{"start":1775832163483,"end":1775832163489}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775832164134,"sessionID":"ses_2882b03e5ffe0qgNxH0zdvDDhW","part":{"id":"prt_d77d8656f001EhILdefa9VCSxC","messageID":"msg_d77d84cae001pTIIWqShkLjL23","sessionID":"ses_2882b03e5ffe0qgNxH0zdvDDhW","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_45f8f4e335c24fbe960bf525","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/session-routing/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/session-routing/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Session Routing — Design\n2: \n3: ## Module\n4: \n5: - Same repository: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` (see sandbox-orchestration design for `go.mod` and versions).\n6: \n7: ## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router`\n8: \n9: ### Config\n10: \n11: ```go\n12: const LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity\"\n13: \n14: type Config struct {\n15:     Port                  string\n16:     Debug                 bool\n17:     EnableTLS             bool\n18:     TLSCert               string\n19:     TLSKey                string\n20:     MaxConcurrentRequests int  // 0 = unlimited at flag level; NewServer coerces to 1000\n21: }\n22: ```\n23: \n24: ### CLI flags (`cmd/router/main.go`)\n25: \n26: | Flag | Default |\n27: |------|---------|\n28: | `-port` | `8080` |\n29: | `-enable-tls` | `false` |\n30: | `-tls-cert` | `\"\"` |\n31: | `-tls-key` | `\"\"` |\n32: | `-debug` | `false` |\n33: | `-max-concurrent-requests` | `1000` (0 means unlimited per flag help; `NewServer` still sets default 1000 when `<= 0`) |\n34: \n35: ### Server struct\n36: \n37: ```go\n38: type Server struct {\n39:     config         *Config\n40:     engine         *gin.Engine\n41:     httpServer     *http.Server\n42:     sessionManager SessionManager\n43:     storeClient    store.Store\n44:     httpTransport  *http.Transport\n45:     jwtManager     *JWTManager\n46: }\n47: ```\n48: \n49: - `httpTransport`: `IdleConnTimeout: 0`, `DisableCompression: false`.\n50: - Store: `store.Storage()` for both session manager and `storeClient`.\n51: - Gin mode: `DebugMode` if `config.Debug`, else `ReleaseMode`.\n52: \n53: ### Route table\n54: \n55: | Method | Path | Middleware | Handler |\n56: |--------|------|------------|---------|\n57: | GET | `/health/live` | none | `handleHealthLive` |\n58: | GET | `/health/ready` | none | `handleHealthReady` |\n59: | GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | `gin.Logger`, `gin.Recovery`, `concurrencyLimitMiddleware` | `handleAgentInvoke` |\n60: | POST | same | same | `handleAgentInvoke` |\n61: | GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | same | `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` |\n62: | POST | same | same | `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` |\n63: \n64: ### SessionManager interface\n65: \n66: ```go\n67: type SessionManager interface {\n68:     GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n69: }\n70: ```\n71: \n72: ### manager implementation (`session_manager.go`)\n73: \n74: ```go\n75: type manager struct {\n76:     storeClient     store.Store\n77:     workloadMgrAddr string\n78:     httpClient      *http.Client\n79: }\n80: ```\n81: \n82: - `NewSessionManager(storeClient store.Store) (SessionManager, error)` reads `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` (required).\n83: - HTTP client: `Timeout: 2 * time.Minute`; transport `MaxIdleConnsPerHost: 100`, `DisableCompression: false`; `http2.ConfigureTransports` with `ReadIdleTimeout: 30s`, `PingTimeout: 15s`.\n84: - Endpoints: `AgentRuntime` → `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/agent-runtime`; `CodeInterpreter` → `.../v1/code-interpreter`.\n85: - Request: `Content-Type: application/json`; optional `Authorization: Bearer` from `loadWorkloadManagerAuthToken()` reading `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` (trimmed); missing file → no header (warning if non-NotExist error).\n86: \n87: ### JWT (`jwt.go`)\n88: \n89: **Constants (unexported unless noted):**\n90: \n91: | Name | Value |\n92: |------|--------|\n93: | `rsaKeySize` | `2048` |\n94: | `jwtExpiration` | `5 * time.Minute` |\n95: | `IdentitySecretName` | `\"picod-router-identity\"` |\n96: | `PrivateKeyDataKey` | `\"private.pem\"` |\n97: | `PublicKeyDataKey` | `\"public.pem\"` |\n98: \n99: ```go\n100: var IdentityNamespace = \"default\" // init: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE if set\n101: ```\n102: \n103: **JWTManager:**\n104: \n105: ```go\n106: type JWTManager struct {\n107:     privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n108:     publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n109:     clientset  kubernetes.Interface\n110: }\n111: ```\n112: \n113: - `NewJWTManager()`: `rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, rsaKeySize)`.\n114: - `GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)`:\n115:   - Base claims: `exp` = now+jwtExpiration (Unix), `iat` = now (Unix), `iss` = `\"agentcube-router\"`.\n116:   - Merges custom claims (e.g. `session_id`).\n117:   - Signing: `jwt.SigningMethodRS256`, signed with RSA private key.\n118: \n119: **Algorithm:** RS256  \n120: **Key type:** RSA 2048-bit, PKCS1 private key PEM (`RSA PRIVATE KEY`), PKIX public key PEM (`PUBLIC KEY`).\n121: \n122: **TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx):**\n123: \n124: - If `clientset == nil`, try `rest.InClusterConfig()`; on failure log warning and return nil (ephemeral keys).\n125: - Else build Secret `IdentitySecretName` in `IdentityNamespace`, type `Opaque`, labels `app=agentcube`, `component=router`, data `private.pem` + `public.pem`.\n126: - Create; on `AlreadyExists`, Get secret and `loadPrivateKeyPEM`.\n127: \n128: ### Reverse proxy\n129: \n130: - `httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy(targetURL)`; `proxy.Transport = s.httpTransport`.\n131: - Director: sets `req.URL.Path` to normalized path, clears `RawPath`, `req.Host = targetURL.Host`, forwarding headers, `Authorization` if JWT non-empty.\n132: - `ModifyResponse`: sets `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n133: - No per-request timeout wrapper (commented-out context timeout in source).\n134: \n135: ### Concurrency middleware\n136: \n137: - Buffered channel size `config.MaxConcurrentRequests`.\n138: - `select`: send to channel or `default` → 429 + abort.\n139: \n140: ### Health JSON shapes\n141: \n142: - Live: `{\"status\":\"alive\"}`.\n143: - Ready OK: `{\"status\":\"ready\"}`.\n144: - Ready fail: `{\"status\":\"not ready\",\"error\":\"session manager not available\"}`.\n145: \n146: ### Error helper (`handleGetSandboxError`)\n147: \n148: - If `apierrors.APIStatus`: use `Status().Code` if non-zero; message from status or `err.Error()`; if code is 500, replace message with `internal server error`; respond `gin.H{\"error\": message}`.\n149: - Else 500 `{\"error\":\"internal server error\"}`.\n150: \n151: ### Environment variables\n152: \n153: | Variable | Used by |\n154: |----------|---------|\n155: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Session manager (required) |\n156: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | JWT secret namespace (optional, default `default`) |\n157: \n158: ### Dependencies (direct use in router)\n159: \n160: - `github.com/gin-gonic/gin`, `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5`, `golang.org/x/net/http2`, `k8s.io/api`, `k8s.io/apimachinery`, `k8s.io/client-go`, `k8s.io/klog/v2`, `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`, `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types`, `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/api`.\n\n(End of file - total 160 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Session Routing — Design\n\n## Module\n\n- Same repository: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` (see sandbox-orchestration design for `go.mod` and versions).\n\n## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router`\n\n### Config\n\n```go\nconst LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity\"\n\ntype Config struct {\n    Port                  string\n    Debug                 bool\n    EnableTLS             bool\n    TLSCert               string\n    TLSKey                string\n    MaxConcurrentRequests int  // 0 = unlimited at flag level; NewServer coerces to 1000","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"specs/session-routing/design.md","time":{"start":1775832164128,"end":1775832164133}}}}
